# Data Management Guidelines

## Adding New Entries to girls.json

When adding new inspiring women to [src/data/girls.json](mdc:src/data/girls.json):

### Required Fields

- `name`: Full name (e.g., "Emma Watson")
- `country`: Country of origin (e.g., "United Kingdom")
- `field`: Professional field (e.g., "Acting & Activism")
- `href`: Wikipedia or reference URL

### Optional Fields

- `image`: Path to image file (e.g., "/images/Emma_Watson.jpg")

### Data Quality Standards

- Use proper capitalization for names and countries
- Be consistent with field descriptions
- Ensure all URLs are valid and accessible
- Use descriptive field names (e.g., "Acting & Activism" not just "Acting")

### Image Guidelines

- Store images in `/public/images/` directory
- Use descriptive filenames (e.g., "Emma_Watson.jpg")
- Optimize images for web use
- Use consistent naming convention: `FirstName_LastName.jpg`
- Support both local images (`/images/name.jpg`) and external URLs

### JSON Structure

```json
{
  "name": "Full Name",
  "country": "Country Name",
  "field": "Professional Field",
  "href": "https://reference-url.com",
  "image": "/images/Image_Name.jpg"
}
```

### Search Compatibility

The search feature automatically searches across:

- Name (case-insensitive)
- Country (case-insensitive)
- Field (case-insensitive)

Ensure data is properly formatted for optimal search results.

